`launchOptions` includes `channel: ''` or similar; use `firefox.launch(launchOptions)`.\n- **Proxy**: The `proxyUrl` is passed in `launchOptions`. The warmup must accept an optional `proxyUrl` parameter (string) and include it in the launch options if provided.\n- Google interactions: navigate to `https://www.google.com`, wait for load, click the search box, type a random benign query (e.g., “Apify web scraping”), simulate typing delay, move mouse randomly, wait for results, dismiss cookie banner if present (`button:has-text('Accetta tutto')` or `button:has-text('Accept all')`), wait 2–3 seconds, then close the page and browser.\n- Use `apify/log` for logging (prefix with `[Warmup]`).\n\n## Action\n\n1. Create file `src/warmup.ts`.\n2. Export an async function with signature:\n   ```typescript\n   export async function warmupBrowser(launchOptions: any, proxyUrl?: string): Promise<void>\n   ```\n   - `launchOptions` is the Camoufox browser launch options object (as used in main.ts).\n   - `proxyUrl` is optional; if provided, it overrides or sets `launchOptions.proxy`.\n3. Inside `warmupBrowser`:\n   - Import `firefox` from `playwright` (or `camoufox-js` – verify which is correct; the project uses `@crawlee/playwright` which internally uses camoufox, but direct launch should use `playwright`). Use `import { firefox } from 'playwright';`.\n   - Merge `proxyUrl` into `launchOptions` if provided.\n   - Log `'[Warmup] Launching browser for warmup…'`.\n   - Launch browser: `const browser = await firefox.launch(launchOptions);`\n   - Create a new context: `const context = await browser.newContext({ viewport: { width: 1280, height: 720 } });`\n   - Create a page: `const page = await context.newPage();`\n   - Log `'[Warmup] Navigating to https://www.google.com'`.\n   - Go to Google: `await page.goto('https://www.google.com', { waitUntil: 'networkidle' });`\n   - Accept cookie consent if present (using Italian locale it might be Italian text – handle both Italian and English).\n   - Wait for search box selector: `input[name=\"q\"]`.\n   - Click on search box, type a query with realistic delays (`page.keyboard.type('Apify web scraping', { delay: 100 })`).\n   - Simulate mouse moves: `await page.mouse.move(100, 200); await page.wait(500);`\n   - Wait for results: `await page.waitForSelector('#search', { timeout: 5000 }).catch(() => {});`\n   - Wait an additional 2 seconds.\n   - Log `'[Warmup] Warmup complete, closing page…'`.\n   - Close page: `await page.close();`\n   - Close browser: `await browser.close();`\n4. Use `try/catch/finally` to ensure browser is always closed even on error.\n5. Log any errors at `warn` level but do not throw – warmup failure should not block the crawl. Log `'[Warmup] Failed but continuing: …'`.\n\n## Reasoning\n\n- Warmup is **mandatory** (not configurable) to improve stealth. By visiting a trusted site like Google with realistic interactions, the Camoufox fingerprint becomes stable and the proxy IP session is active before hitting target sites.\n- Using the same `launchOptions` ensures the browser configuration (window size, locale, humanization, proxy) is identical to the crawler, preventing fingerprint inconsistencies.\n- The function is standalone so it can be called from `main.ts` easily without modifying crawler internals.\n- Graceful error handling avoids aborting the crawl if Google is unreachable.\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n- **File**: `src/warmup.ts`\n- **Imports**:\n  ```typescript\n  import { firefox } from 'playwright';\n  import log from 'apify/log';\n  ```\n- **Function signature** as above.\n- Use `await page.waitForTimeout()` (or `page.wait(ms)` – Playwright 1.60 uses `page.waitForTimeout`).\n- Google cookie dismiss: try `button:has-text('Accetta tutto')` then `button:has-text('Accept all')`.\n- Typing: use `page.keyboard.type()` with delay.\n- Mouse move: use `page.mouse.move()` with random coordinates.\n- **No extra dependencies**.\n\n## Error Handling and Edge Cases\n\n- **Google not loading**: catch `TimeoutError` or other navigation errors, log warning, close browser, return normally. The crawl should proceed.\n- **Proxy errors**: if proxy fails, the warmup may fail; same handling – log warning, continue.\n- **Browser launch failure**: rare; log error and continue (crawler will launch its own browser later).\n- **Multiple warmups**: if called multiple times (not expected), each will launch a separate browser. OK.\n- **No proxyUrl provided**: use `launchOptions` as given (may already contain proxy from main.ts).\n\n## Validation\n\n- After implementation, verify the module can be imported without errors.\n- Run `npx tsx src/warmup.ts` (temporary test script) – should open and close Google successfully in headless mode.\n- Check that logs appear correctly with `[Warmup]` prefix.\n- Ensure no dangling browser processes remain after function returns (closed in `finally`).\n\n## Dependencies and Inputs\n\n- **Inputs**: `launchOptions` object (from main.ts), optional `proxyUrl` string.\n- **Dependencies**: `playwright` (already installed), `apify/log` (already installed).\n- **No new npm packages**.\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Must be ESM (type:module). Use `import` not `require`.\n- Follow project code style: single quotes, no `any` (use proper types from Playwright). For `launchOptions` use `import type { LaunchOptions } from 'playwright'`.\n- The function must **not** throw; any error must be caught and logged.\n- Keep code concise – no unnecessary abstractions.\n\nThis is the ONLY task you must complete in this iteration. Do not work on other steps.",
